      "I really don't like the fact that we automatically recurse into arrays. It\r\njust make things complicated and can easily have undesired results.\r\n\r\nIs there a reason why we want to automatically recurse into arrays for\r\nnested fields?\r\nOn Jun 20, 2013 6:41 PM, \"Michael Lucy\" <notifications@github.com> wrote:\r\n\r\n> Alright, here's what we settled on:\r\n>\r\n>    - pluck will accept both => true and => [:a, :b, :c] (i.e. we use\r\n>    arrays to specify the union of one or more paths).\r\n>    - We will automatically recurse into arrays.\r\n>    - We will, at some point in the future, introduce r.number, r.array,\r\n>    etc. and people can use them in paths passed to e.g. has_fields or\r\n>    with_fields to get schema enforcement.\r\n>\r\n> \8212\r\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub<https://github.com/rethinkdb/rethinkdb/issues/889#issuecomment-19794308>\r\n> .\r\n>"
